UPDATE public.questions SET
  stimulus_text = 'It is commonly believed that the best way to improve the quality of a product is to focus on the process of its creation. However, recent research suggests that focusing on the outcome of a product can also improve its quality. In one study, researchers asked participants to create origami cranes and instructed half of the participants to focus on the process of folding the paper, while instructing the other half to focus on the outcome of creating a beautiful crane. The results showed that the participants who focused on the outcome were more likely to produce a high-quality crane. This finding suggests that focusing on the outcome of a product can lead to higher-quality results, even though the process of creation is often emphasized as being the most important factor in quality improvement.',
  question_text = 'In this passage, the phrase "even though" most likely indicates that the author believes that',
  stimulus_type = NULL,
